INTRODUCTION
This document is the Work Instruction (WI) for Document Management
PURPOSE
This WI defines the steps that are followed to add, update and monitor the
documents inside the organization.
SCOPE
The WI applies to the QMSrs Tool set that accompanies this WI

DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT PROCESS
This section displays the flow of the process of document management.
DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT WORK INSTRUCTION
CREATE A DOCUMENT
This section explains how to index any document in the QMS.
To create a document:
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Create a Document’.
 Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk ‘*’ and any other fields you
have data for.
 Click on save icon “ ” to save changes that appears at the top of the
window.
Document Entry Fields
Below are the fields to be completed when adding a document to documents list.
Field Name
Description

Insert the ID of the document.

MANAGE DOCUMENTS
In this section the user can edit, delete and use the filter to search documents using
varying criteria.
EDIT A DOCUMENT
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage Documents’.
 Click on edit icon“ “beside the document that you want to edit.
 Make the necessary changes.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
DELETE A DOCUMENT
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage Documents’.
 Click on delete icon “ “beside the document that you want to delete.
 To delete the document click on “OK “or “Cancel “to cancel deleting.
SEARCH A DOCUMENT
Origination Date
Select the issue date from the calendar

search criteria you choose.
CREATE NEW DCR
This section explains how to create document change request. Anyone in the
organization who has access to the QMS can raise a DCR
To create new DCR:
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS
 Select “Create DCR”.
 Fill the mandatory fields with the red asterisk ‘*’ and any other fields you
have data for.
 Click on save icon “ ” to save changes that appears at the top of the
window.

MANAGE DCR
In this section the user can edit a DCR, add approval members to DCR (when the
status of the DCR is open) or use the filter to search a DCR using varying criteria.
EDIT DCR
DCR Details
Document No.
Click on search sign" " to choose the document then
select from the drop down list or enter the number
manually then click on "Enter" from the keyboard
DCR Type
Select the type from the drop-down list
Origination Date
Select the origination date from the calendar
Document File URL
Enter the link of the document in the following format:
http://www.google.com
Document File
Insert the file of document to load it.
DCR Originator
Click on search sign" " to choose the originator from
the drop down list.
DCR Owner
Click on search sign" " to choose the owner from the
drop down list.
Reason for Change
Enter the reason to support the DCR

 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.

 Click on edit icon“ “beside the DCR that you want to edit if the status of

 Make the necessary changes.

ADDING APPROVAL MEMBERS
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage DCR’.
 Click on edit icon“ “beside the DCR that you want to edit (if the status of
the DCR is open).
 Click on" Approval Members" tab then click on add icon“ “.
 Double click on the field under 'Member ' and select the name from the drop
down list.
 Double click on the field under 'Type' and select the type from the drop down
list.
 Click on “Save “to save the amended data or “Cancel” to cancel the changes.
* 'Approval Status' and 'Decision Details' fields will be filled later from DCR Approvals
section by the member whom you add and responsible for the decision.

 Click on Approval Members tab then click on delete icon“ “beside the

SEARCH DCR
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Manage DCR’.
 Click on filter icon “ “at the top of the window, then select the search
criteria.
 Fill the text field or select from the drop down list which depends on the
search criteria you choose.
 After finding the DCR, you can view and edit its details.
APPROVE DCR
This section explains how to approve a DCR
To approve a DCR:
 Go to Document Management section in the QMS.
 Select ‘Approve DCR'.

REPORTS
VIEW DOCUMENTS
In this section the user can view all the documents with the RAG status to prioritise
and to use the filter with its different search criteria as follows:
 Click on filter icon “ “at the top of the window, then select the search
criteria.
 Fill the text field or select from the drop down list which depends on the
search criteria you choose.
 Select from the drop down list and click on next icon" ".
 To clear the result of filtration click on delete filter icon" ".
User can export the report as below:
 Click on export icon" "to export the data into different format (Xls. PDF...)
